$ SVG/JavaScript example: access-root-element

gh|about-svg|/javascript/embedded/access-root-element.html||

Note: the value of the `data` attribute of the `<object>` elements is the name of an → design/graphic/svg[SVG] file (that was created with → design/graphic/inkscape[Inkscape]).

gh|about-svg|/javascript/embedded/img/access-root-element.png||


Apparently, this example does not work if run on a local file system because (for security reasons?) `getSVGDocument` returns `null` in such a case. Instead, the example must be run
over HTTP.

sa:

  → development/web/DOM/examples/Node/Document/documentElement[`document.documentElement()`] returns a documents root element.

  → design/graphic/svg/examples/javascript/

  → design/graphic/svg/examples/[SVG examples]
